%N A365743 Triangle T(n,k) read by rows: row n has length 2*n-1, gand is generated by T(1,1)=0, T(n,1)=T(n-1,1)+3, T(n,2)=T(n,1)-1, and for k>=3, T(n,k)=3*T(n-1,k-2)+1.
%C A365743 The sequence is a permutation of all integers >= 0.
%C A365743 Each row of T contains n*2-1 terms.
%C A365743 T(1,1) = 0; T(2,1) = T(1,1)+3; T(2,2) = T(2,1)-1; T(2,3) = 3*T(1,1)+1 = 1 ("knight jump").
%C A365743 Right diagonal is A003462.
%C A365743 The first two columns increase by 3^1, the next two columns by 3^2, and so on.
%F A365743 T(n,k) = ((12*n - 6*k - 3 + (-1)^k)/2 * 3^((2*k - 3 - (-1)^k)/4) - 1)/2.
%F A365743 T(n,k) = T(n-1,k) + 3^ceil(k/2).
%e A365743 Triangle T(n,k) begins:
%e A365743 n/k 1| 2| 3| 4| 5| 6| 7| 8| 9|
%e A365743 1|  0
%e A365743 2|  3  2  1
%e A365743 3|  6  5 10  7  4
%e A365743 4|  9  8 19 16 31 22 13
%e A365743 5| 12 11 28 25 58 49 94 67 40
%e A365743 6| 15 ...
%o A365743 (PARI) { local( T(n, k) = if(k<=2, 3*(n-1)+1-k, 3*T(n-1, k-2)+1) ); for(n=1, 8, for(k=1, 2*n-1, print1(T(n, k), ", ")); print); }
